Carnitas are normally boiled in melted fat - lard, but these special carnitas are boiled in avocado oil 🥑 making them less greasy and loaded with flavor! With @mexi_papa_adventures and @jeffrey_merrihue 

📍 When you’re in #Phoenix, don’t miss @mexicancorral #MexicanFood #Arizona #carnitas

node.text: The best way to get your morning started in Mae Hong Son (แม่ฮ่องสอน) is with a bowl of noodles and yellow split pea porrdige with fried tofu. Add a little chili oil, and it's warming and tasty! You'll find this at the morning market. #ShanFood #MaeHongSon #Thailand #streetfood

node.text:
The Shan / Thai Yai (ไทใหญ่) donuts are made with rice flour and coconut, and black sesame, deep fried, and soaked in a sugar cane syrup bath, almost jalebi style. I'm not hugely into sweets, but these were game changing. Crunchy, sweet, juicy, and fragrant. #ShanFood #MaeHongSon 

📍 Homestay in Muang Pon village - โฮมสเตย์ป้าคำหลู่ บ้านโบราณร้อยปี

node.title: Might Be the World's Best Donuts!! 🍩

node.text:
Tea leaves on their own, have a bitter astringent taste. But mixed with shallot oil, chilies, garlic, chicken, lime juice, and sugar, it was a brilliant balance of taste. #BanRakThai #MaeHongSon #Thailand

📍 LiXian Restaurant, Ban Rak Thai (บ้านรักไทย), Thailand

node.text: These slabs of pork are cured in the morning dew for 30 days. The result is a dry aged complexity somewhere between ham and bacon with a slight sourness - AMAZING. You'll find it in Ban Rak Thai (บ้านรักไทย) village in Mae Hong Son, via Yunnan. Best sliced and fried, or stir fried with local pickled greens. #BanRakThai #บ้านรักไทย #MaeHongSon

#Tucson #Arizona #MexicanFood
